<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-21-0589 </DOCNO><TEXT>Three cases of ruptured aneurysms of the digestive arteries are reportedand the different available radiological methods leading to the diagnosisare discussed. Computed tomography and selective arteriography seem tobe the methods of choice in this condition. Since the patients do notusually present typical signs until the aneurysm ruptures, the diagnosisis late. Early management of these patients is necessary in order todecrease the mortality rate.</TEXT></DOC>